# car-retail — Senior Next.js Fullstack

Read `docs/project-context.md` (admin spec + asset checklist), `docs/techstack.md`, `docs/implementation-plan.md` before feature work. Application code lives in `web/`.

## Stack

Next.js 15 App Router · JavaScript · CSS Modules · Prisma · PostgreSQL · Cloudflare R2 · next-intl · in-memory cache only (no Redis).

## Routing

- Public: `web/app/[locale]/` (`vi` default, `en`)
- Admin: `web/app/admin/` (no locale prefix)
- English paths differ: `/vi/dang-ky-lai-thu` ↔ `/en/book-test-drive`
- Slugs per locale in DB: `slug: { vi, en }`

## Data & i18n

- Descriptions/slugs: `{ vi, en }` JSON in PostgreSQL
- Attributes: `[{ key, value, unit }]` only — no locale on values
- Units: DB array `{ key, value: { vi, en } }`
- API returns `{ units, attributes }` — no `label`/`display` from server
- Labels: `web/messages/[locale].json` → `spec.*`
- Fallback: empty `en` → show `vi`

## External services (.env only)

- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL
- `STORAGE_S3_*` — Cloudflare R2 via `web/lib/r2.js`
- Never hardcode endpoints; no Redis, no MinIO in Compose

## Code style

- Server Components default; `"use client"` only for forms, switcher, carousel
- CSS Modules + `globals.css`; mobile-first; no CSS-in-JS
- ES modules; no TypeScript in v1
- Media → R2 only; metadata in `media_assets` table
- Cache: `web/lib/cache.js`, `unstable_cache`, `revalidateTag` on admin writes

## Docker

Compose: `app` + `migrate` only. No postgres/redis/minio services.

## Post-implementation review

After completing a feature (or meaningful slice), before marking it done:

1. **Run the project** — `cd web && npm run dev` (or `docker compose up`); confirm DB/env are up. **Use port 3000** — if something is already listening on 3000, terminate that process first, then start dev on 3000 (do not silently fall back to 3001).
   - Windows (PowerShell): find PID with `Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 3000 | Select-Object -ExpandProperty OwningProcess -Unique`, then `Stop-Process -Id <pid> -Force`
   - macOS/Linux: `lsof -ti :3000 | xargs kill -9` (or equivalent)
2. **Playwright UI test** — use the Playwright MCP to exercise the affected public/admin flows in the browser (happy path + one failure/edge case when relevant).
3. **Fix** — resolve any UI, routing, i18n, or console errors found; re-run Playwright on touched flows until clean.
4. **Log** — note what was tested and any deferred issues in the execution log.

Do not skip this for non-trivial UI work; trivial doc-only changes are exempt.

